profile_positions.description:
We’re Adevinta, a global leader in digital marketplaces. Our household brands, including Marktplaats in the Netherlands, mobile.de in Germany and leboncoin in France, reach hundreds of millions of people every month.

Key responsibilities:

- Partner with the local markets to provide local legislative/policy knowledge;
- Responsible for individual case management when it comes to complex employee cases such as long-term sickness;
- Act as an escalation point for complex employee lifecycle matters such as performance conversations, burn-out preventions, any other HR process/policy related topics;
- Provide local language support for queries and with handling local documentation;
- Manage any local, legal and regulatory query management that is unable to be resolved by People Services Team;
- Work with the Employee Relations and Case Management team within People Operations, to provide any local Labour and Works Council considerations for employee relations cases that are being managed within their region or team;
- Work with the People Business Partner to help on complex employee cases and to partner with the local business and its leaders.

Key responsibilities:

• execute supported employee onboardings based on the Dutch labour legislation and setup and enroll payroll and benefits;
• create, maintain and archive compliant local employment contracts and employment documentation based on Dutch labour legislation;
• support and document the entire employee life cycle;
• ensure supported employees are appropriately set up in all Velocity Global systems;
• research and respond to all benefits, international payroll, expense reporting and all other HR matters;
• responsible for continuously updating the company knowledge base for the Netherlands;
• support our client service team across all aspects of the business;
• drive employee satisfaction and retention, troubleshooting within our Dutch entity;
• communicate with domestic and foreign embassies om immigration matters;
• support and execute upon compliant terminations and offboardings based on the Dutch labour legislation;
• develop and maintain competency in the area of international employment.
